{"ts":"2026-06-27T10:54:39.992Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"8xwv46ka","input":{"summary":"I have created and updated the Pydantic schemas for the GFF AI portal and admin APIs as requested.\n\n### Steps taken and Implementation:\n1. **Inspected Existing Files**: Reviewed `backend/app/models/` to discover the exact database fields for all MVP models (`User`, `ClientAccount`, `Project`, `AgentOperation`, `DocumentItem`, `Invoice`, `SupportTicket`, `GovernanceItem`).\n2. **Created Modular Schemas**:\n   - Created the following new files under `backend/app/schemas/` containing `*Base`, `*Create`, `*Update`, and `*Response` (using `from_attributes = True` for Pydantic v2):\n     - `client_account.py`\n     - `project.py`\n     - `agent_operation.py`\n     - `document_item.py`\n     - `invoice.py`\n     - `support_ticket.py`\n     - `governance_item.py`\n     - `auth.py` (containing `LoginRequest`, `TokenResponse`, and `CurrentUserResponse`)\n3. **Updated Existing User Schema**: Updated `backend/app/schemas/user.py` to support `UserUpdate` and expand `UserResponse` with more fields mapped to the model, while maintaining backwards compatibility for existing schemas and routes.\n4. **Exposed Schemas**: Updated `backend/app/schemas/__init__.py` to cleanly import and export all new model schemas and authentication schemas.\n5. **Verified Security**: Ensured that no response schema exposes `hashed_password` or `password` fields.\n6. **Validation**: Ran backend import checks for both schemas and the overall application router. The entire FastAPI system imports perfectly without issues.","verified":true}}}
